  "prompt": "If I removed my laptop non removable battery would it work on AC or battery must be plugged in?",
  "response": "If you remove the **non-removable battery** from your laptop, it will **not work**, even if it is plugged into an AC power source. Here\u2019s why:\n\n1. **Non-Removable Battery Design**: Laptops with non-removable batteries are designed to rely on the battery as part of the power delivery system. Even when plugged into an AC adapter, the laptop typically draws power through the battery or requires the battery to be present for proper operation.\n\n2. **Power Management**: The laptop\u2019s power management system expects the battery to be connected. Removing the battery could cause the system to fail to boot or shut down immediately.\n\n3. **Safety Concerns**: Most laptops with non-removable batteries are not designed to operate without the battery. Attempting to remove the battery could also damage the laptop\u2019s internal components.\n\nIf you need to remove or replace the battery in a laptop with a non-removable battery, it is recommended to do so only through professional repair services to avoid damaging the device. If the battery is faulty, it\u2019s best to get it repaired or replaced by a qualified technician.",
